.Dd May 8, 1995
.Dt DF 1
.Os BSD 4
.Sh NAME
.Nm df
.Nd display free disk space
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm df
.Op Fl kP
.Op Ar file | Ar filesystem ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm Df
displays statistics about the amount of free disk space on the specified
.Ar filesystem
or on the filesystem of which
.Ar file
is a part.
Values are displayed in 512-byte per block block counts.
If neither a file or a filesystem operand is specified,
statistics for all mounted filesystems are displayed
(subject to the
.Fl t
option below).
.Pp
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl k
Displays sizes in kilobytes (1024-byte blocks) instead of the default
blocksize of 512 bytes.
.It Fl P
Displays in the exact format described by the
.St -p1003.2
specification.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr getmntinfo 3 ,
.Xr fstab 5 ,
.Xr mount 8
.Sh HISTORY
A
.Nm df
command appeared in
.At v6 .
